1. After you complete the task, always check all rules in .windsurfrules file and make sure you followed them.
2. Don't make explanation comments in code, if there are remove them.
3. Always use Qwik solutions for building the website or solve issues in a Qwik-friendly way.
4. Functions should not have more than two nested "if" conditions; if necessary, split the function into smaller ones.
5. Use double quotes for strings.
6. Consider performance;
7. Solve all issues in a Qwik-friendly way.
8. Always think about whether it is appropriate to use useEffect, useLayoutEffect, or useCallback.
9. Use TypeScript for type safety and better code quality.
10. Use proper error boundaries to handle errors in a Qwik-friendly way.
11. Emphasize clean code practices.
12. Don't create TS and eslint ignore comments, solve problems.
13. Do not make declarations without reading the values.
14. Remove unused declarations in imports.
15. Always set complete dependency arrays.
16. Don't remove custom comments.
17. Add JS doc for all components, types and functions or hooks.
18. Don't remove previous working code, and don't change anything what I don't ask to change.
19. Avoid infinite loops.
20. Don't ask me if I want to remove a file, you can do it by yourself.
21. After you complete the task, run browser MCP and check if everything works as expected.
